NOTICE — Original DECWAR Source (1978–79)

This TypeScript port (the "Software") is a re-implementation of DECWAR, the
18-player Federation-vs-Empire space-combat game written 1978–79 for the
DEC PDP-10 at the University of Texas (the "Original Source"). Game mechanics,
formulas, RNG behavior, message text, and other product elements are derived
from the Original Source and are reproduced under the good-faith belief that
the Original Source was distributed for academic and hobbyist use without
restriction (via the DECUS tape exchange and successor channels).

The Original Source files (located under
`../decwar source and associated files/`) retain their original authors'
attribution and are NOT covered by the MIT grant above. They are included in
this repository as historical reference material, in the `utexas/utexas23-reconstruction/`
reconstruction tree. The Original Source's specific license terms are
**not formally verified** as of this writing; if you intend to redistribute
or build upon those files (as opposed to this TS port), confirm their
disposition with the original authors or the University of Texas first.

This port deliberately excludes the CompuServe-era (DrForbin/Merlyn) edits
that may carry separate commercial-distribution terms — see `PORT.md`
§"What was simplified" and `../analysis/12-cross-agent-reconciliation.md` §7.

If you are an original author or contributor and want the attribution
clarified, expanded, or corrected, please open an issue or contact the
maintainer.
